  "text": "After estimation of the PDC, null hypothesis of |π i←j (f )| = 0 tests can be performed for each frequency and each channel pair at 5%. It can be rejected if the estimated PDC exceeds a threshold value calculated by the Patnaik approximation of quantile thresholds, utilizing χ 2 υ distribution with non-integer υ, which can be computed using the gamma function [CITATION_1] . Fig. 3 . The most ten significant effective connectivity during the left-hand motor imagery and right-hand motor imagery respectively, and the directional connectivity represented by the red arrows.",
